<TITLE> 'Top city terror' killed in RAB encounter </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 14 (bdnews24.com)Twenty-six year old Abu Bakar Siddiqui Ronnie, aka 'Red Ronnie', said to be a "top terror" of the capital's notorious Hazaribagh area, was killed in an encounter with Rapid Action Battalion on Monday. Ronnie, was shot dead in the early hours at Chandrima Real Estate area next to the Mohammadpur flood control embankment, said RAB-2 operations officer Talebur Rahman Rahman told bdnews24.com that a RAB team in plain clothes approached the spot, acting on a tip-off that a criminal gang was gathered there, when the gang fired shots at them. RAB men returned fire and after a 5-6 minute exchange, the gang fled leaving the dead body of Ronnie behind, said Rahman. The law enforcers searched the spot and found a pistol, empty Phensidyl bottles, empty beer cans and marijuana, the RAB official said. Rahman said Ronnie, "a top terror" of the city's crime-ridden Hazaribagh, had links to the outlawed Gono Bahini (People's Army) and had been facing six cases including murders. bd
